SENATE AND ASSEMBLY, DO ENACT AS FOLLOWS:
1 Section 1. NRS 679A.210 is hereby amended to read as follows:
2 679A.210 1. Notwithstanding any other provision of law, an insurer,
3 including, without limitation, an insurer listed in NRS 679A.160, shall not issue or
4 renew a policy of liability insurance that contains a provision that:
5 [1.] (a) Reduces the limit of liability stated in the policy by the costs of
6 defense, legal costs and fees and other expenses for claims; or
7 [2.] (b) Otherwise limits the availability of coverage for the costs of defense,
8 legal costs and fees and other expenses for claims.
9 2. The provisions of this section do not apply to:
10 (a) A risk retention group, as defined in NRS 695E.110.
11 (b) Captive insurance that does not cover third-party liability.
12 (c) A nonadmitted insurer, as defined in NRS 685A.0375.
13 3. As used in this section, “policy of liability insurance” includes only a
14 policy of casualty insurance that:
15 (a) Provides insurance against legal liability arising from the ownership or
16 operation of a motor vehicle, as defined in NRS 485.050;
17 (b) Provides insurance against legal liability arising from the ownership of
18 housing that is occupied by the owner as the primary residence of the owner;
19 (c) Is a policy of commercial general liability insurance;
20 (d) Is a policy of commercial automobile insurance; or
21 (e) Provides insurance covering the professional liability of a provider of
22 health care, as defined in NRS 41A.017.
